OL,3,CTop KGB defector Oleg Gordievsky dies
OL,4,Caged 86
OL,6,FIn the early 1980s he was able to warn
OL,7,Fthe West that fears among the paranoid
OL,8,FSoviet leadership of a surprise Nato
OL,9,Fnuclear attack had brought the two
OL,10,Fsides perilously close to war,
OL,11,Fprompting US President Ronald Reagan
OL,12,Fto dial down his anti-USSR rhetoric.
OL,14,FHis intelligence was subsequently
OL,15,Fcrucial in guiding Margaret Thatcher
OL,16,Fin her early contacts with the
OL,17,Freformist Mikhail Gorbachev, whose
OL,18,Fascent to power helped bring the Cold
OL,19,FWar to a close.
