OL,3,CTop KGB defector Oleg Gordievsky dies
OL,4,Caged 86
OL,6,FBut in 1985, just as he had been
OL,7,Fappointed to the key post of head of
OL,8,Fthe KGB residency in London, he came
OL,9,Funder suspicion as a British spy.
OL,11,FSummoned back to Moscow where he was
OL,12,Fdrugged and interrogated, he quickly
OL,13,Frealised that his life was in danger
OL,14,Fand he needed to escape.
OL,16,FUsing a long pre-arranged plan, a
OL,17,Fsignal was relayed to his MI6 handlers.
